  "prompt": "What do I do with my useless life?",
  "response": "Feeling like your life is \"useless\" is a heavy and painful emotion, and it\u2019s important to approach this with compassion and care. Everyone struggles with moments of feeling lost or unfulfilled, but these feelings don\u2019t define your worth or potential. Here are some steps to help you find meaning and direction:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**\n   - It\u2019s okay to feel this way, and you\u2019re not alone. Many people go through similar struggles. Acknowledging your emotions is the first step toward healing.\n   - Journaling or talking to someone you trust can help you process your thoughts.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Practice Self-Compassion**\n   - Be kind to yourself. Avoid harsh self-criticism and remind yourself that everyone has value, even if it\u2019s not immediately clear.\n   - Celebrate small wins, no matter how insignificant they may seem.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Seek Meaning in Small Things**\n   - You don\u2019t need to find a grand purpose right away. Start by finding joy or meaning in small, everyday activities\u2014like helping someone, spending time in nature, or creating something.\n   - Volunteering or helping others can give you a sense of purpose and connection.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Set Small, Achievable Goals**\n   - Break down what you want into manageable steps. Whether it\u2019s learning a new skill, improving your health, or reconnecting with friends, small goals can build momentum.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Explore Your Interests**\n   - What excites or intrigues you? Try new hobbies, read, take classes, or explore creative outlets. Discovering what you enjoy can bring renewed energy to your life.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Connect with Others**\n   - Isolation can deepen feelings of worthlessness. Reach out to friends, family, or support groups. Building relationships can remind you that you\u2019re not alone.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Consider Professional Help**\n   - If these feelings persist, a therapist or counselor can provide tools and support to help you navigate them. There\u2019s no shame in seeking help\u2014it\u2019s a courageous step toward healing.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Challenge Negative Thoughts**\n   - When you feel like your life is \"useless,\" question that thought. What evidence contradicts it? What small things have you done that matter, even if they seem minor?\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Focus on Growth, Not Perfection**\n   - Life doesn\u2019t need to be perfect or extraordinary to be meaningful. Growth, learning, and connection are valuable in themselves.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Remember: Your Life Has Value**\n   - Even if you can\u2019t see it right now, your existence matters. You have unique experiences, talents, and potential that the world needs.\n\n---\n\nTake things one step at a time. You don\u2019t have to have all the answers right now. Healing and finding purpose is a journey, and it\u2019s okay to take it slowly. You\u2019re not alone, and there is hope. \u2764\ufe0f",
  "temperature": 1.0,
